'''Mohamed Abdelmonem El-Sayed Mohamed Ahmed''' ({{langx|ar|مُحَمَّد عَبد الْمُنْعِم السَّيِّد مُحَمَّد أَحمَد}}; born 1 February 1999) is an Egyptian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{French football updater|Nice}} club [[OGC Nice|Nice]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].

==Club career==
Abdelmonem started his career at [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]], where he achieved several local and continental trophies. He scored a crucial equalizer against [[Wydad AC]] in the [[2023 CAF Champions League final]] second leg which helped his team winning the title by 3–2 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/668083 |title=Al Ahly beat holders Wydad to win CAF Champions League |publisher=ESPN |date=11 June 2023 }}</ref> Furthermore, he was loaned out to [[Smouha SC|Smouha]] and [[Future FC|Future]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2020/01/26/salah-mohsen-abdelmonem-loan-smouha/ |title=Al Ahly duo Salah Mohsen, Abdelmonem loaned out to Smouha|publisher=Kinfut |date=26 January 2020 }}</ref>

On 29 August 2024, Abdelmonem joined [[Ligue 1]] side [[OGC Nice|Nice]] by signing a contract until 2028.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ogcnice.com/en/article/127449/mohamed-abdelmonem-joins-les-aiglons.html |title=Mohamed Abdelmonem joins Les Aiglons |publisher=OGC Nice |date=29 August 2024 }}</ref> A few days later, on 1 September, he made his debut as a substitute in a 4–1 away win over [[Angers SCO|Angers]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/6/53/531114/Sports/Talents-Abroad/Egypt%E2%80%99s-Abdelmonem-makes-Nice-debut.aspx |title=Egypt's Abdelmonem makes Nice debut |publisher=Ahram Online |date=1 September 2024 }}</ref> On 25 April 2025, he sustained an [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|ACL injury]] during a 3–1 away win over [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]], which would sideline him for several months.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ahmed |first=Saher |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2025/04/27/mohamed-abdelmonem-suffers-acl-injury-faces-lengthy-layoff/ |title=Mohamed Abdelmonem Suffers ACL Injury, Faces Lengthy Layoff |publisher=KingFut |date=27 April 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Abdelmonem represented [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] in [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/59818147 |title=Afcon 2021: Aston Villa's Trezeguet returns to join Salah and Elneny in Egypt squad |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=29 December 2021 |access-date=29 December 2021 |archive-date=31 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211231083437/https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/59818147 |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023]] Africa Cup of Nations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://english.ahram.org.eg/News/514851.aspx|title=Egypt coach Vitoria announces final squad for AFCON 2023; veterans El Shahat and El-Said left out|publisher=[[Al-Ahram]]|last=Elassal|first=Mahmoud|date=30 December 2023|access-date=30 December 2023}}</ref>

